    <text id="R155939T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate Secretary of War Judah P. Benjamin notifies General Thomas J. Jackson
                    that he will be sending troops through Staunton to join him in November,
                1861.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Gen. T. J. JACKSON, Winchester, Va.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-11-06">November 6, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">RICHMOND,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>I have ordered your old brigade to be sent to you at once from Centreville and
                    McLaughlin's company of Rockbridge artillery, and had already ordered a further
                    force of about 6,000 men to be detached from Loring's command and to join you,
                    by way of Staunton, before receiving your letter brought by Col. Preston. Will
                    send you full instructions by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>J. P. BENJAMIN,<lb/> Acting Secretary of War.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
